        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 6:13PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 612 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Berclair, or 13 miles northeast of Beeville, moving west at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Berclair.

This includes US Highway 59 between mile markers 676 and 692.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
